Tell HN: Exercism needs donations to survive 2023
text:
As a regular user of exercism.io, I am a little worried to see this banner at the top of their homepage which says: "Exercism needs donations to survive 2023. Please support us if you can!". Their donations page says they have 965 donors and they have recieved donations of $32,837.10 since September 2021. I think they could use more help, especially from corporations that have some budget to support such initiatives.

I am worried about the future of this very useful resource for beginners, and I hope they get enough funding to continue the great work they are doing.

Full disclosure: I am not involved with exercism.io in any way except for being a regular user. Wanted to share this only because it saddens me to imagine a future in which excersim.io no longer exists.

Treefrog Editor (now Edita) update
text:
I've been using Edita as my only code editor for over 12 months now, so I thought it was time for an update.

Most of the work over the last year has been focused on improving stability, usability, and performance. As well as fixing tons of little bugs, I've rewritten the renderer multiple times to make it as fast as possible (currently getting 80-160fps on a 10kloc file on an old i5), and done large-scale refactorings to keep the codebase nice and flexible.

Feature-wise the biggest addition is the Refactor tab, which uses CodeMatch syntax [1] to perform arbitrary transformations with a live preview pane.

My process so far has been to simply use the editor and work on whatever feels like it most needs attention. Now that it's reasonably stable I think it would be a good time to get some more feedback from other devs to see what would make it a viable daily driver. There are no doubt many glaringly missing features and unclear UI elements that I just don't notice, so please point these out!

Site (very WIP): https://edita.vercel.app

Original HN post: https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=29787861

HN post for CodeMatch: https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=34424767

[1]: https://codematch-gamma.vercel.app/

Ask HN: How do you migrate Email and Exchange accounts
text:
Hey guys,

Im looking for tools to use in order to migrate a small amount (around 50) mailboxes from an MS Exchange hoster, to Office 365.

Most of the hard part has been synced already, but now iam at the point where i have drift between the "old" and "new" mailbox because the migration took way longer than expected.

My Ideal software would probably run in a container, but my main concern is that the tool needs to either run with a (modest) cloud fee or at least on linux so i can configure it myself. I dont have a problem with paying for good software, but as the org im representing right now is german, the tool needs to adhere to GDPR too.

What are you using? And why?
